    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Harsh comments on Hamas</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: The Palestinian Authority President had strong criticism and a firm demand for Hamas.</strong></p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Palestinian Authority President Mahmoud Abbas had some harsh words for Hamas. He urged the group to release Israeli hostages and halt measures that provoke Israel's bombings of Gaza, calling Hamas "<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-04-2025-h3-4-sons-of-dogs" target="_blank">sons of dogs</a>". He also called for Gaza's demilitarization, a demand Hamas has rejected. Hamas fears this would let Israel take complete control of the territory.
        </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Abbas used his speech to outline his vision for a Palestinian state and also called on Israel to halt its military operations. However, his political opponent, Mustafa Barghouti, criticized his comments as "totally inappropriate." He said, ‚ÄúThe last thing that anybody should accept is to blame the victims for the aggression they are subjected to.‚Äù</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Hamas ousted the PA in 2007. However, they want a role in Gaza's governance after the war ends. Hamas has <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-04-2025-h3-met-some-resistance" target="_blank">met some resistance</a> in the last month from Gazans who started protesting their rule. Meanwhile, Egypt and Qatar are working on a ceasefire and hostage agreement, but progress is slow. Since mid-March, over 1,600 Palestinians have died in Israeli airstrikes. Currently, 59 Israeli hostages are still held by Hamas, with 24 thought to be alive.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The Palestinian Authority (PA) is the government body that exercises partial civil control over the Palestinian enclaves in the Israeli-occupied West Bank. </p>
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>
